Normally we encourage newly submitted packages to be at   0.99.z when submitting to Bioconductor  so that 1.0.0  represents the release of the package in Bioconductor.
We have made a few exceptions to this and your reviewer assigned can assist you with this.  Generally if you would like to try to submit with a different version number make note of the reason when you submit your package.


